## 5. Performance Tips

Running spring physics for hundreds of features at 60fps requires care:

1. **TypedArrays** — `Float64Array` instead of regular arrays. The JIT optimizes typed array access into near-native speed.
2. **`map.project()` is fast** — converting lng/lat to screen pixels every frame sounds expensive, but MapLibre's projection is heavily optimized. 600 hexes × 60fps = 36,000 projections/sec runs fine.
3. **Conditional updates** — only call `setFeatureState` when the height actually changes:

```javascript
if (Math.abs(vel[i]) > 1 || Math.abs(curH[i] - target) > 1)
  map.setFeatureState({source, id: i}, {h: curH[i]});
```

4. **Single source, multiple layers** — both your main layer and any glow/shadow layers can read from the same source + feature-state. One update animates everything.

