## 6. Make It Your Own

The entire visualization is a **single HTML file** — no build step, no npm, no framework. Fork it and swap in your own data:

- 🏙️ **Building heights** from OpenStreetMap
- 📊 **Census demographics** (income, education, population density)
- 🌡️ **Climate data** (temperature anomalies, rainfall)
- 🚗 **Traffic density** from GPS traces
- 📱 **App usage metrics** by geography

The spring animation pattern works with ANY MapLibre fill-extrusion source. The hex binning is just one option — you could use census tracts, zip codes, H3 cells, or custom polygons.

